2500|$|The rapid {{response}} of Kennedy's [...] "Robert Bork's America" [...] speech stunned <b>the</b> <b>Reagan</b> <b>White</b> House; though conservatives considered Kennedy's accusations slanderous ideological smears on a well qualified {{candidate for the}} bench, the attacks went unanswered {{for two and a}} half months. Bork refused to withdraw himself and his nomination was rejected 58–42. Anthony Kennedy was eventually confirmed in his place.|$|E
